ADDITIONAL TERMS FOR THE CODEX

The file `codex/codex.txt` contains the 5QLN Codex Appendix A canonical
form (the "Codex"). The Codex is additionally published under the 5QLN Open
Source License at https://www.5qln.com/5qln-open-source-license/.

The Codex's 217 canonical bytes may not be modified except by the V.L.5(b)
tri-condition gate documented in GOVERNANCE.md. Any implementation of 5QLN
must reproduce the canonical SHA-256 hash:

    feaa46b4147d4e023cdd3fd59c051d063e8ec654ee7b38a481dcd5e4c781859b

Implementations producing any other hash are not 5QLN, regardless of any
other claim of conformance.

